bib_record.title: Isobaric analog resonances in proton scattering from Te124, Te126, Te128, and Te130

free_txt: Four solid-state detectors.
The beam energy was calibrated by using the 27Al(p,n)
threshold at 5.803 MeV: the absolute uncertainty in
the calibration is about 25 keV.
Targets consisted of separated tellurium isotopes
evaporated onto carbon backings. Target thicknesses of
the order of 50 mu-g/cm2 tellurium on 15 mu-g/cm2
carbon.
The relative experimental errors are
caused by target inhomogeneity and changes in solid
angle as the beam wanders over the target. Absolute
cross sections are believed to be good to 10%.
Fig.1 in Phys.Rev.,175,1498,1968 was
digitized by GSYS2.4.7.
